==English==
===Etymology 1===
Anglo-Norman ''[[sever]]'', Old Northern French ''[[sewiere]]'' ‘overflow channel for a fishpond’.

====Pronunciation====
*(''[[RP]], US''): {{AHD|/so͞o'ə/}}, {{IPA|/ˈsuːə/}}, {{SAMPA|/"su:@/}}
*:'''Homophones''': [[suer]]<!--one who sues-->
*(''dated RP''): syo͝oə, /ˈsjʊə/, /<tt>"sjU@</tt>/

====Noun====
{{en-noun}}

# A [[pipe]] or system of pipes used to remove human [[waste]] and to provide [[drainage]].

=====Translations=====

'''pipe or system of pipes used to remove human waste and to provide drainage'''
